      "writtenOn": "2017-04-19T20:42:53Z",
      "side": 0,
      "message": "\u003e Chromium will not be entering this branch since the destination will not be kIndex_8_SkColorType.\n\u003e So perhaps removing this is incorrect. Please advise.\n\u003e \n\u003e But the gif spec says any given frame can not fill the entire canvas.\n\u003e If the first frame has a disposal method other than keep, does that mean later frames could also require the fill color?\n\nSure, later frames could require the fill color, but if the client requests Index8 for a later frame, we will have returned a failure before we reach here. If the client requests kN32 (as they should), we\u0027ll bypass this block and return SK_ColorTRANSPARENT, which is correct.",
      "parentUuid": "798a79de_33802aa8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 502,
        "startChar": 51,
        "endLine": 502,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "96d5b9a273a5513fb3215fc06452cda82c3d6872",
